title: For Sale:  ESEE AH-1 Survival Arrowhead With Kydex Sheath and Military Dogtag Chain
postcontent:
This post is for one New in the Box ESEE AH-1 Survival Arrowhead with Handmade and Fitted Kydex Sheath with Military Dogtag Neck Chain and ESEE Survival Card.
All Brand New Items Included In Sale:

1- ESEE AH-1 Survival Arrowhead With Factory Box 
2- Handmade Three or Four Eyelet Kydex Sheath (Buyer's Choice)
3- Military Dogtag Chain and Key Chain
4- ESEE Survival Card
5- ESEE Sticker

These are brand new ESEE AH-1 arrowheads and have only been removed from the box to mold the kydex to each blade, attach the chain and polish the edge.
They are made from 1095 high carbon steel, which is the same steel used in many of the best knives in service today. They are also covered by ESEE's unconditional lifetime warranty, should you somehow break it. As a free service to all buyers, I will professionally hone your AH-1 to a mirror shine.

*Please note, these arrowheads will not in any way sharpen to a razor's edge without serious reprofiling of the blade. I have completely stripped the powder coating off one and reprofiled the blade and even then will not shave hair as well as most blades.*

The triangle shaped three eyelet or square shaped four eyelet sheaths are the available sheath shape options. I plan to have other colors available soon but at the present time only have black kydex.

There are several ways to carry your new ESEE arrowhead. The most common is like a necklace or "neck knife" with the provided dogtag chain threaded through one or more eyelets and worn around the neck. Other ways include as a keychain or simply dropping it in a pocket or purse secured in the sheath without the chain attached.

I have included a few pictures of another optional way to carry your new arrowhead. I have one lashed to the front of my personal Becker Necker. (The Becker knife, sheath, paracord etc. is not included in this sale.)  is a handy way to keep it close at hand but out of the way until it is needed and since both are secured to my belt, there is little chance of losing them.

I am asking $25 for Knoxville or surrounding area.  I'd be happy to ship if you will pay $2 for shipping with tracking. 

Thanks and let me know if you have any questions.
Steve

title: For Sale:  BRAND NEW--Kahr CM9 9mm Luger pistol Style # CM9093
location: Livingston Manor NY area, Hudson Valley, New York
postcontent:
The CM Series takes the value priced features from Kahr's CW series (3.6" barrel 9mm, .40 S&W and .45 ACP models) and incorporates these features into a smaller 3" barrel package. The CM9093 has the same external dimensions as the PM9093 which make it ideal for concealed carry by licensed civilians and law enforcement personnel. The CM9093 is chambered in a 9 x 19 caliber, has a 3.0" barrel and an overall length of 5.42, with a height of 4.0". The pistol weighs in at 14 ounces plus 1.9 ounces for the 6 rd stainless steel magazine. Differences between the CM models and PM models are the CM9093 has a conventional rifled barrel instead of the match grade polygonal barrel on Kahr's PM series; the CM slide stop lever is MIM (metal-injection-molded) instead of machined; the CM series slide has fewer machining operations and uses simple roll marking instead of engraved markings and finally the CM series are shipped with one magazine instead of two magazines.

Kahr's seven patents are incorporated into the CM9093 resulting in benefits not available in other compact semi-autos on the market today. The black polymer frame features patented 4140 steel inserts molded into the frame in the front and back for added rigidity and strength which can withstand firing thousands of rounds. Kahr's incomparable cocking cam trigger system employs a patented cam to both unlock the firing pin block (passive safety) and complete cocking and releasing of the firing pin. The system provides a "safe-cam action" and unbelievably smooth double action only trigger stroke, fast to fire in critical defensive situations.

Kahr's two patents covering the offset recoil lug and the trigger bar attachment allow Kahr's barrel to fit lower in the frame and since there is no hammer the shooter's hand is further up the grip resulting in less felt recoil and quick follow-up shots. The CM9 boasts real sights which are drift adjustable in the rear and a pinned-in polymer front sight featuring a white bar-dot configuration. Finally the slide locks back after firing the last round - another feature missing on a number of lower cost compact semi-auto pistols.

The CM9 slide is only .90 inch wide and machined from solid 416 stainless slide with a matte finish, each gun is shipped with one 6 rd stainless steel magazine with a flush baseplate. Magazines are USA made, plasma welded, tumbled to remove burrs and feature Wolff Gunsprings. The magazine catch in the polymer frame is all metal and will not wear out on the stainless steel magazine after extended use.

Kahr offers the CM series at a great value price but did not compromise on the features, accuracy or reliability found in all Kahr pistols.

title: For Sale:  German Airpistol
postcontent:
Weihrausch HW40PCA .22 cal. air pistol.  This is a single stroke pneumatic airgun similar to the Beeman P3, except in .22 instead of .177.  Adjustable sights.  Purchased from Pyramid Air about five years ago for about $225.00.  Included with pistol:  Doskocil lockable hard case, will fit any service size pistol - 3-1/2 cans of RWS Meisterkugeln match wadcutter pellets (approx. 1800 pellets) - mounted 1-1/2 power pistol scope.  Extremely accurate, wonderful trigger action.  Please note:  this is a great pistol for plinking, training, or target shooting, but it is NOT suitable for pest control, squirrel hunting, or the like.  The velocity is just not high enough.  If you are not familiar with single stroke pneumatic air guns, some of the pluses are:  quiet, no recoil or vibration whatsoever, no springs to wear out or take a set, consistent velocity, great accuracy.  They do not, however, work for very high velocity field use.  Excellent condition.  I can't send pictures, so don't ask.  Many suppliers are now selling a very low price spring BB gun that looks a lot like this one - they are NOT the same.  I'm retired, so I can meet you at your convenience so you can examine the pistol.

Cash sale, or will trade for .9mm practice ammo.  How much ammo depends on what kind you have.  NO reloads.  NO Tula or the various color "Bears" from our friends in the former Warsaw Pact.  I really don't like leaving the range covered with soot and smelling like a tire fire.  Various bullet weights (full boxes only) are okay, because I'm trying to determine a best load for a new pistol.
